    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>chicken</strong> to a clean chopping board, cover with <strong>cling film</strong> and bash with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until flattened to approx. 1cm thickness</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-and-romesco-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>flattened chicken</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-and-romesco-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for 10-12 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the pasta, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> (save the pot!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-and-romesco-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-and-romesco-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot<strong> </strong>to a medium heat with drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-and-romesco-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>reserved starchy water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>tomato paste </strong>and <strong>romesco sauce </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chicken stock </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and stir it all together</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-and-romesco-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooked pasta </strong>and <strong>wilted spinach </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy romesco spaghetti</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-and-romesco-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> cooked chicken</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> creamy romesco spaghetti </strong>and top with the <strong>sliced chicken</strong></p><p>Finish with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
